@criccomini @alexvanboxel Thanks for the quick response, I've locally verified the JavaOperator (see attached)
![sjunqw9rccy](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/24922485/22347707/cf08e02c-e3bd-11e6-8a3d-2f909e2bca18.png)
 but happy to make fixes if others see issues due to this change.

@bolkedebruin will be more descriptive.

@aoen num_runs is not respected when there is no valid dag file present.  

For example, this newly added test case https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/blob/master/tests/jobs.py#L1251 assumes the scheduler would terminates after 1 run.
However, when dag files are absent (or invalid), _file_paths (https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/blob/master/airflow/utils/dag_processing.py#L639) is empty and num_runs doesn't make sense any more.

@aoen we can do that, but I guess the bigger question is what's the definition of num_runs when dag file is absent.

`      :param num_runs: The number of times to try to schedule each DAG file.
        -1 for unlimited within the run_duration.`
